A 26-year-old man was arrested in connection with the murder of his 18-month-old stepson, Western Cape police said on Monday. Police spokeswoman, Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana, said officers were informed by workers at a health facility near Kensington of a toddler who died after being brought in with serious injuries to the head and body. The child s 26-year-old stepfather was arrested and his 30-year-old mother taken in for questioning, said Rwexana. The suspect was due to appear in the Cape Town Magistrate s Court once charged. ALSO READ: WCape police investigate murder after a body of girl, 5, found in Strand &nbsp;